notesStmt.note: Title from caption heading after introduction (p. 31); author from colophon (p. 343).
Incipit: Postquam in institutione philosophicam rudem totius philosophiae ad umbrationem tradidimus... (p. 1).
Explicit: ... quod Platoni et talibus visum est. Finis totius Logicae. Scripsit Mavinus Nicolaus Denise anno d[omi]ni millesimo septingentesimo tertio (p. 343).

msContents.summary: Commentary on Aristotle's works of logic.
msContents.textLang: Latin, with engravings captions in French

msItem.title: Commentarii in universam Aristotelis philosophiam, p. 1
Commentarii in universam Aristotelis Logicam, p. 31

supportDesc.extent: 172 leaves : 210 x 160 (172 x 115) mm. bound to 218 x 172 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 172; [xiv], 1-30, [ii], 31-216, [ii], 217-260, [ii], 261-269, 290-337, 339-343, [vi]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners. Engravings not numbered.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by what appears to be a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Full page engravings of a female allegorical figure, "La Logique" (opposite p. 1); "Aristote" (opposite p. 31); "Platon" (opposite p. 217); and "Zenon" (opposite p. 261). All but the first have biographical captions in French and are signed "chez H. Bonnart au Coq." The plate of "La Logique" has an almost identical match in Ms. Codex 273.

history.provenance: Sold by Jeffrey D. Mancevice (Worcester, Mass.), Jan. 15, 2002.
